ending on whether fallback triggers. Added unit tests for validate_mail_inbox_limit. Latest rch cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-cli --tests still fails outside this slice due to unrelated workspace errors in sqlmodel-frankensqlite (Arc<str>/Arc<[u8]> conversions) and mcp-agent-mail-core/src/atc_admissibility.rs.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:40:20Z"},{"id":1272,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Random deep-dive pass: traced share/export pipeline (CLI -> snapshot -> scrub -> bundle -> finalize) for context, then focused on mcp-agent-mail-core ATC modules because atc_admissibility.rs contained a broken denial-code path. Fixed evaluate_admissibility to map failed gates to the actual DenialCode enum via a dedicated helper, added coverage for non-high-risk exploration budget exhaustion, and removed an unused variable in atc_voi_control.rs. Verification via rch: cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib --tests = OK; cargo test -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib atc_admissibility -- --nocapture = 14 passed.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:46:16Z"},{"id":1273,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Deep fellow-agent review pass: fixed two concrete regressions and re-validated touched slices. (1) crates/mcp-agent-mail-core/src/atc_admissibility.rs had a broken denial path using an undefined variable and nonexistent DenialCode variants; replaced it with explicit gate->denial mapping and added low-risk exploration-budget coverage. (2) crates/mcp-agent-mail-server/src/tui_compose.rs still treated char indices as terminal cell widths after the Unicode subject-count fix; wide characters could misplace cursors and overflow bordered inputs. Added width-aware truncation/cursor math and a regression test. Also tightened body byte-limit enforcement so multibyte chars cannot push drafts past MAX_BODY_LEN during typing. Reviewed current tui_bridge/tui_events diffs too; no new obvious defect there. Verification: rch cargo check -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib --tests = OK; rch cargo test -p mcp-agent-mail-core --lib atc_admissibility -- --nocapture = 14 passed; rustfmt --edition 2024 --check on touched files = OK. Server rch checks remain blocked by upstream sqlmodel-frankensqlite Arc<str>/Arc<[u8]> type errors, not by these local changes.","created_at":"2026-03-19T19:55:14Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.3.1.1","title":"Tracker blocker: classify live beads DB sidecars versus preserved recovery artifacts","description":"Distinguish the currently relevant live database state from preserved historical rebuild or orphan artifacts under .beads. The output should identify which files are evidence, which are stale debris, and which ones br doctor is actually complaining about today.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:45.312405542Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:53.880724262Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:53.880032217Z","close_reason":"Completed: distinguished the live beads.db WAL-sidecar anomaly from preserved historical recovery artifacts","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blockers","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1.1","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:41:45.312405542Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.3.1.2","title":"Tracker blocker: define safe non-destructive remediation path for stale beads recovery debris","description":"After the artifact classification is done, document a safe remediation policy that does not require deleting anything during the audit. Include what can be ignored, what should be quarantined later with explicit approval, and what would justify escalation.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:42:00.171611958Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:47:04.888550523Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T23:47:04.887932135Z","close_reason":"Completed: documented safe non-destructive remediation policy for the tracker anomaly during the audit","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","blockers","tooling"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:42:00.171611958Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1261,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.1.2","author":"ubuntu","text":"Safe remediation policy for the current audit: do not delete any .beads artifacts manually; treat the WAL-without-SHM condition as non-blocking only while sqlite integrity, DB-vs-JSONL counts, and br doctor write_probe remain green; serialize br mutations to one writer at a time; if the anomaly worsens or counts diverge, stop tracker writes, preserve the current .beads state, and use br doctor --repair during a quiet window instead of ad hoc cleanup. Historical .bad/.rebuild/.br_recovery files require explicit human approval before any deletion or archival action.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:46:56Z"}]}
 {"id":"br-97gc6.3.2","title":"Blockers: reconcile discrepancy between br dep cycles and bv graph health","description":"br dep cycles reports cycles while bv --robot-triage reported has_cycles=false. Determine which view is stale or filtered, then create or link concrete follow-up work for any real cycle removal needed.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:53.637418176Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:23.897562656Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["beads","bv","graph"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.2","depends_on_id":"br-97gc6.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:06:53.637418176Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1259,"issue_id":"br-97gc6.3.2","author":"ubuntu","text":"Evidence on 2026-03-18: br dep cycles returned 8 cycles, but every bead in those cycles is closed (br-246y, br-2avs, br-3c7vp, br-3ibsu, br-dsdzo, br-2ei.5, br-2ei.5.7, br-2ei.5.7.1-.7.4, br-3vwi.6.2, br-3vwi.7, br-3vwi.7.5). This currently looks like a scope mismatch between historical all-issue cycle detection and bv triage on actionable/open graph state, not a live open-work cycle.","created_at":"2026-03-18T23:44:23Z"}]}
